A/B Testing

  1. H√†m t√≠nh AB testing cho 2 nh√≥m b·∫±ng ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p permutation test theo trung b√¨nh v√† t·ª∑ l·ªá
permutation_test_mean <- function(x, y, R, alter){
  output_list <- list()
  df <- split(x, y)
  nA <- length(df[[1]])
  nB <- length(df[[2]])
  n <- nA + nB
  mean_diff <- numeric(R)
  set.seed(45)
  for (i in 1:R){
    idx_A <- sample(x = 1:n, size = nA)
    idx_B <- setdiff(x = 1:n, y = idx_A)
    mean_diff[i] <- mean(x[idx_A]) - mean(x[idx_B])
  }
  output_list$res_perm <- mean_diff
  meanA <- mean(df[[1]])
  output_list$mean_A <- meanA
  meanB <- mean(df[[2]])
  output_list$mean_B <- meanB
  if (alter == 'left'){ p_value <- mean(mean_diff < (meanA - meanB)) }
  else if (alter == 'right'){ p_value <- mean(mean_diff > (meanA - meanB)) }
  else{ p_value <- mean(abs(mean_diff) > abs(mean1 - mean2)) }
  output_list$p_value <- p_value
  return(output_list)
}

permutation_test_prop <- function(x, y, R, alter){
  output_list <- list()
  df <- split(x, y)
  nA <- length(df[[1]])
  nB <- length(df[[2]])
  n <- nA + nB
  prop_diff <- numeric(R)
  set.seed(45)
  for (i in 1:R){
    idx_A <- sample(x = 1:n, size = nA, replace = TRUE)
    idx_B <- setdiff(x = 1:n, y = idx_A)
    prop_diff[i] <- mean(x[idx_A]==0) - mean(x[idx_B]==0)
  }
  output_list$res_perm <- prop_diff
  propA <- mean(df[[1]]==0)
  output_list$prop_A <- propA
  propB <- mean(df[[2]]==0)
  output_list$prop_B <- propB
  if (alter == 'left'){ p_value <- mean(prop_diff < (propA - propB)) }
  else if (alter == 'right'){ p_value <- mean(prop_diff > (propA - propB)) }
  else{ p_value <- mean(abs(prop_diff) > abs(propA - propB)) }
  output_list$p_value <- p_value
  return(output_list)
}
  1. H√†m chia nh·ªè d·ªØ li·ªáu v√† t√≠nh p-value c·ªßa m·ªói batch
permutation_chisq <- function(x, y, R, batch_size) { 
  contingency_table <- table(x, y) 
  chi_squared_obs <- chisq.test(contingency_table)$p.value 
  chi_squared_permute <- numeric(R) 
  num_batches <- ceiling(length(x) / batch_size)
  p_value_permute <- numeric(num_batches)
  for (j in 1:num_batches) {
    df <- data.frame(x = x, y = y)
    df <- sample(df)
    start_idx <- (j - 1) * batch_size + 1
    end_idx <- min(j * batch_size, length(x))
    x_batch <- x[start_idx:end_idx]
    y_batch <- sample(y[start_idx:end_idx])
    contingency_table_batch <- table(x_batch, y_batch)
    p_value_permute[j] <- chisq.test(contingency_table_batch)$p.value
  }
  list(Observed_Chi_Squared = chi_squared_obs, 
       P_Value = p_value_permute)
}

1. V·∫•n ƒë·ªÅ s·ª©c kh·ªèe v√† t√¨nh tr·∫°ng b·ªánh l√Ω

1.1. Bi·∫øn nh·ªã ph√¢n

M·ª•c ti√™u : Ki·ªÉm tra li·ªáu t·ª∑ l·ªá KH√îNG m·∫Øc b·ªánh ti·ªÉu ƒë∆∞·ªùng c√≥ b·ªã ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng b·ªüi hai nh√≥m ng∆∞·ªùi m·∫Øc v√† kh√¥ng m·∫Øc c√°c v·∫•n ƒë·ªÅ s·ª©c kh·ªèe v√† t√¨nh tr·∫°ng b·ªánh l√Ω

Gi·∫£ thuy·∫øt v√† ƒê·ªëi thuy·∫øt:\[ H_0 : p_0 = p_1 \]

\[ H_1 : p_0 \neq p_1 \]

M·ª©c √Ω nghƒ©a : \(\alpha = 0.05\)

M√¥ t·∫£ v√† ki·ªÉm ch·ª©ng :

par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
for (name in c('high_bp', 'high_chol', 'stroke', 'heart_diseaseor_attack', 'diff_walk')){
  cat("\n", name)
  print(table(data[[target_var]], data[[name]]))
  res <- permutation_test_prop(data[[target_var]], data[[name]], 1000, "two-sided")
  
  hist(res$res_perm, col = "skyblue", xlab = paste("p_value =", res$p_value), ylab = "Frequency", main = name)
}

K·∫øt lu·∫≠n : V·ªõi m·ª©c √Ω nghƒ©a 0.05, b√°c b·ªè ƒë∆∞·ª£c \(H_0\) hay c√°c b·ªánh l√Ω nh∆∞ cao huy·∫øt √°p, cao cholesterol, ƒë·ªôt qu·ªµ, ƒëau tim, kh√≥ khƒÉn v·ªÅ v·∫≠n ƒë·ªông ƒë·ªÅu ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn t√¨nh tr·∫°ng b·ªánh ti·ªÉu ƒë∆∞·ªùng.

Nh·∫≠n x√©t : Ng∆∞·ªùi m·∫Øc c√°c b·ªánh l√Ω nh∆∞ tr√™n c√≥ nguy c∆° cao m·∫Øc b·ªánh ti·ªÉu ƒë∆∞·ªùng h∆°n ng∆∞·ªùi kh·ªèe m·∫°nh.

2. Li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn ch·∫•t l∆∞·ª£ng cu·ªôc s·ªëng v√† s·ª©c kh·ªèe t√¢m l√Ω

2.1. Bi·∫øn nh·ªã ph√¢n

M·ª•c ti√™u : Ki·ªÉm tra li·ªáu t·ª∑ l·ªá KH√îNG m·∫Øc b·ªánh ti·ªÉu ƒë∆∞·ªùng c√≥ b·ªã ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng b·ªüi hai nh√≥m ng∆∞·ªùi c√≥ l·ªëi s·ªëng kh√°c nhau hay kh√¥ng.

Gi·∫£ thuy·∫øt v√† ƒê·ªëi thuy·∫øt:\[ H_0 : p_0 = p_1 \]

\[ H_1 : p_0 \neq p_1 \]

M·ª©c √Ω nghƒ©a : \(\alpha = 0.05\)

M√¥ t·∫£ v√† ki·ªÉm ch·ª©ng :

par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
for (name in c('smoker', 'hvy_alcohol_consump', 'no_docbc_cost', 'chol_check', 'phys_activity', 'fruits', 'veggies', 'any_healthcare')){
  cat("\n", name)
  print(table(data[[target_var]], data[[name]]))
  res <- permutation_test_prop(data[[target_var]], data[[name]], 1000, "two-sided")
  
  hist(res$res_perm, col = "skyblue", xlab = paste("p_value =", res$p_value), ylab = "Frequency", main = name)
}

# V·∫Ω ma tr·∫≠n t∆∞∆°ng quan c√°c bi·∫øn v·ªõi BMI
# T√≠nh ma tr·∫≠n t∆∞∆°ng quan ch·ªâ v·ªõi c√°c bi·∫øn s·ªë
cor_matrix <- cor(data_no_diabetes[sapply(data_no_diabetes, is.numeric)])

# L·∫•y gi√° tr·ªã t∆∞∆°ng quan v·ªõi BMI
cor_bmi <- cor_matrix["bmi", ]

# Chuy·ªÉn th√†nh dataframe ƒë·ªÉ v·∫Ω
cor_bmi_df <- data.frame(Variable = names(cor_bmi), Correlation = cor_bmi)

ggplot(cor_bmi_df, aes(x = reorder(Variable, Correlation), y = Correlation, fill = Correlation)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_flip() +  # Xoay tr·ª•c ƒë·ªÉ c√°c bi·∫øn hi·ªÉn th·ªã d·ªçc
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", mid = "gray", high = "red", midpoint = 0) +
  labs(title = "Correlation with BMI", x = "Variables", y = "Correlation") +
  theme_minimal()

  • Nh·∫≠n x√©t chung:

    • Gen_hlth c√≥ t∆∞∆°ng quan cao nh·∫•t v·ªõi BMI v√† l√† y·∫øu t·ªë quan tr·ªçng ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI => ƒêi·ªÅu n√†y h·ª£p l√Ω v√¨ s·ª©c kh·ªèe t·ªïng qu√°t th∆∞·ªùng ph·∫£n √°nh c√°c y·∫øu t·ªë li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn c√¢n n·∫∑ng v√† l·ªëi s·ªëng.

    • High_bp v√† Diff_walk: Hai y·∫øu t·ªë n√†y c√≥ m·ªëi t∆∞∆°ng quan ƒë√°ng k·ªÉ v·ªõi BMI =>cho th·∫•y nh·ªØng ng∆∞·ªùi c√≥ BMI cao th∆∞·ªùng g·∫∑p c√°c v·∫•n ƒë·ªÅ v·ªÅ huy·∫øt √°p v√† kh·∫£ nƒÉng di chuy·ªÉn.

    • Phys_hlth v√† High_chol: C≈©ng c√≥ m·ªëi quan h·ªá ƒë√°ng k·ªÉ v·ªõi BMI => ƒêi·ªÅu n√†y h·ª£p l√Ω v√¨ BMI cao c√≥ th·ªÉ d·∫´n ƒë·∫øn c√°c v·∫•n ƒë·ªÅ s·ª©c kh·ªèe nh∆∞ cholesterol cao v√† s·ª©c kh·ªèe th·ªÉ ch·∫•t suy gi·∫£m.

    • Nh√≥m y·∫øu t·ªë c√≥ t∆∞∆°ng quan th·∫•p v·ªõi BMI: Phys_activity, Education, Income, v√† Fruits c√≥ t∆∞∆°ng quan r·∫•t th·∫•p, g·∫ßn nh∆∞ kh√¥ng ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë√°ng k·ªÉ ƒë·∫øn BMI.

    • C√°c y·∫øu t·ªë t∆∞∆°ng quan √¢m v·ªõi BMI:Phys_activity c√≥ t∆∞∆°ng quan √¢m nh·∫π, cho th·∫•y ng∆∞·ªùi ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông th·ªÉ ch·∫•t nhi·ªÅu c√≥ xu h∆∞·ªõng BMI th·∫•p h∆°n.

3.2 Ki·ªÉm tra c√°c bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c trong m√¥ h√¨nh ban ƒë·∫ßu

B√¢y gi·ªù ch√∫ng ta s·∫Ω ti·∫øn h√†nh ki·ªÉm tra c√°c bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c n√†y c√≥ th·∫≠t s·ª± ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI kh√¥ng

# H√†m ki·ªÉm tra t∆∞∆°ng t√°c
evaluate_interaction <- function(interaction_term, data) {
  # T√°ch c√°c bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c
  interaction_vars <- strsplit(interaction_term, ":")[[1]]
  
  # X·ª≠ l√Ω t√™n bi·∫øn n·∫øu l√† factor
  interaction_vars <- sapply(interaction_vars, function(var) {
    if (is.factor(data[[var]])) {
      paste0(var, levels(data[[var]])[2])  
    } else {
      var
    }
  })
  
  # Gh√©p l·∫°i t√™n bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c
  interaction_term_formatted <- paste(interaction_vars, collapse = ":")
  
  # X√¢y d·ª±ng c√¥ng th·ª©c
  formula <- as.formula(paste("bmi ~", interaction_term, "+ high_bp + high_chol + chol_check + smoker + stroke + ",
                              "heart_diseaseor_attack + phys_activity + fruits + veggies + ",
                              "hvy_alcohol_consump + any_healthcare + gen_hlth + ment_hlth + ",
                              "phys_hlth + diff_walk + age + sex + education + income"))
  
  # Ch·∫°y m√¥ h√¨nh
  model <- lm(formula, data = data)
  summary_model <- summary(model)
  
  # Ki·ªÉm tra n·∫øu bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c t·ªìn t·∫°i trong b·∫£ng coefficients
  if (interaction_term_formatted %in% rownames(summary_model$coefficients)) {
    p_value <- summary_model$coefficients[interaction_term_formatted, "Pr(>|t|)"]
  } else {
    p_value <- NA  # G√°n NA n·∫øu kh√¥ng t·ªìn t·∫°i
  }
  
  return(list(term = interaction_term, p_value = p_value))
}

# Danh s√°ch c√°c bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c c·∫ßn ki·ªÉm tra
interaction_terms <- c(
  "high_bp:high_chol", "high_bp:chol_check", "high_bp:phys_activity", "high_bp:hvy_alcohol_consump", 
  "high_bp:gen_hlth", "high_bp:diff_walk", "high_chol:smoker", "high_chol:phys_hlth", 
  "smoker:fruits", "smoker:veggies", "smoker:gen_hlth", "smoker:diff_walk", 
  "chol_check:gen_hlth", "chol_check:age", "stroke:gen_hlth", "stroke:phys_hlth"
)

# Ch·∫°y ki·ªÉm tra t·ª´ng bi·∫øn t∆∞∆°ng t√°c
results <- lapply(interaction_terms, evaluate_interaction, data = data_no_diabetes)

# Chuy·ªÉn k·∫øt qu·∫£ th√†nh dataframe ƒë·ªÉ xem
results_df <- do.call(rbind, lapply(results, as.data.frame))

# In k·∫øt qu·∫£
print(results_df)

4. L·ª±a ch·ªçn m√¥ h√¨nh

# S·ª≠ d·ª•ng model.matrix ƒë·ªÉ chuy·ªÉn c√°c bi·∫øn factor sang d·∫°ng dummy
data_no_diabetes_dummy <- model.matrix(
  ~ high_bp * high_chol + high_bp * phys_activity + high_bp * hvy_alcohol_consump +
    high_bp * gen_hlth + high_bp * diff_walk + high_chol * smoker +
    smoker * fruits + smoker * veggies + smoker * gen_hlth +
    smoker * diff_walk + chol_check * age + stroke * gen_hlth + stroke * phys_hlth +
    heart_diseaseor_attack + education + income + sex - 1,  # -1 ƒë·ªÉ lo·∫°i b·ªè intercept t·ª± ƒë·ªông
  data = data_no_diabetes
)

# Chuy·ªÉn ƒë·ªïi ma tr·∫≠n sang data frame
data_no_diabetes_dummy <- as.data.frame(data_no_diabetes_dummy)
data_no_diabetes_dummy$bmi <- data_no_diabetes$bmi  # Th√™m bi·∫øn ph·ª• thu·ªôc
library(leaps)

# √Åp d·ª•ng regsubsets v·ªõi d·ªØ li·ªáu ƒë√£ chuy·ªÉn ƒë·ªïi
out_subset_bmi <- regsubsets(
  bmi ~ ., 
  data = data_no_diabetes_dummy, 
  nvmax = 20,  # S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng bi·∫øn t·ªëi ƒëa
  method = "seqrep"
)

# V·∫Ω bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì Mallows' Cp

  cp_values, 
  type = "b",

best_model_index <- which.min(cp_values)
print(paste("S·ªë bi·∫øn trong m√¥ h√¨nh t·ªët nh·∫•t:", best_model_index))
## [1] "S·ªë bi·∫øn trong m√¥ h√¨nh t·ªët nh·∫•t: 21"

set.seed(123)

# 10-fold cross-validation
error10 <- errorest(best_model_formula, data = data_no_diabetes_dummy, model = lm)$error

# 5-fold cross-validation
error5 <- errorest(best_model_formula, data = data_no_diabetes_dummy, model = lm, est.para = control.errorest(k = 5))$error

# 50-fold cross-validation
error50 <- errorest(best_model_formula, data = data_no_diabetes_dummy, model = lm, est.para = control.errorest(k = 50))$error

# T·ªïng h·ª£p k·∫øt qu·∫£ RMSE
cv_errors <- data.frame(
  k = c(5, 10, 50),
  RMSE = c(error5, error10, error50)
)
print("Sai s·ªë RMSE t·ª´ Cross-Validation:")

=> Ch√∫ng ta v·∫´n s·∫Ω gi·ªØ m√¥ h√¨nh ban ƒë·∫ßu

5. Ch·∫©n ƒëo√°n m√¥ h√¨nh

5.1 Ki·ªÉm tra t√≠nh tuy·∫øn t√≠nh c·ªßa m√¥ h√¨nh

ggplot(data = md_bmi_update, mapping = aes(x = .fitted, y= .resid)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", se = FALSE) + # ve duong cong theo xu huong dl
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(x= "Fitted values", y= "Residuals") +
  theme_bw()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Nh·∫≠n x√©t:

  • ƒê∆∞·ªùng cong m√†u xanh cho th·∫•y c√≥ s·ª± dao ƒë·ªông nh·∫π xung quanh ƒë∆∞·ªùng ngang t·∫°i gi√° tr·ªã 0.
  • M·∫∑c d√π ph·∫ßn l·ªõn c√°c ph·∫ßn d∆∞ n·∫±m kh√° ƒë·ªìng ƒë·ªÅu xung quanh gi√° tr·ªã 0, nh∆∞ng ·ªü m·ªôt s·ªë khu v·ª±c, ƒë·∫∑c bi·ªát ·ªü ph√≠a ƒë·∫ßu v√† cu·ªëi c·ªßa gi√° tr·ªã Fitted Values, c√≥ d·∫•u hi·ªáu c·ªßa s·ª± kh√¥ng tuy·∫øn t√≠nh nh·∫π.

5.2 Ki·ªÉm tra ƒë·ªìng nh·∫•t ph∆∞∆°ng sai

ggplot(md_bmi_update, aes(x = .fitted, y = sqrt(abs(.stdresid)))) +
  geom_point(na.rm = TRUE) +
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", na.rm = TRUE, se = FALSE) +
  labs(x = "Fitted Values", y = expression(sqrt("|Standardized residuals|"))) +
  theme_bw()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Nh·∫≠n x√©t: ƒê·ªìng nh·∫•t ph∆∞∆°ng sai: Kh√¥ng c√≥ d·∫•u hi·ªáu r√µ r√†ng c·ªßa vi ph·∫°m ƒë·ªìng nh·∫•t ph∆∞∆°ng sai trong m√¥ h√¨nh. Ph∆∞∆°ng sai ph·∫ßn d∆∞ d∆∞·ªùng nh∆∞ kh√¥ng thay ƒë·ªïi l·ªõn theo gi√° tr·ªã d·ª± ƒëo√°n (.fitted).

5.3 Ki·ªÉm tra ph√¢n ph·ªëi c·ªßa ph·∫ßn d∆∞

# Ph·∫ßn d∆∞ t·ª´ m√¥ h√¨nh
residuals <- resid(md_bmi_update)

# Histogram c·ªßa ph·∫ßn d∆∞
hist(residuals, breaks = 30, main = "Histogram of Residuals",
     xlab = "Residuals", col = "lightblue", border = "black")

# Q-Q Plot
qqnorm(residuals, main = "Q-Q Plot of Residuals")
qqline(residuals, col = "red", lwd = 2)

  • Ph·∫ßn gi·ªØa c·ªßa d·ªØ li·ªáu (g·∫ßn tr·ª•c 0 tr√™n tr·ª•c x):

    • C√°c ƒëi·ªÉm n·∫±m kh√° s√°t ƒë∆∞·ªùng th·∫≥ng m√†u ƒë·ªè (ƒë∆∞·ªùng chu·∫©n l√Ω thuy·∫øt)

      => ƒêi·ªÅu n√†y cho th·∫•y ph·∫ßn d∆∞ g·∫ßn trung t√¢m tu√¢n theo ph√¢n ph·ªëi chu·∫©n.

  • Ph·∫ßn ƒëu√¥i (·ªü hai ƒë·∫ßu c·ªßa bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì):

    • ·ªû ƒëu√¥i b√™n tr√°i (gi√° tr·ªã r·∫•t nh·ªè) v√† ƒëu√¥i b√™n ph·∫£i (gi√° tr·ªã r·∫•t l·ªõn), c√°c ƒëi·ªÉm l·ªách kh·ªèi ƒë∆∞·ªùng th·∫≥ng chu·∫©n m·ªôt c√°ch r√µ r·ªát.

      => ƒê√¢y l√† d·∫•u hi·ªáu c·ªßa ph√¢n ph·ªëi kh√¥ng chu·∫©n ·ªü ph·∫ßn ƒëu√¥i => Vi ph·∫°m gi·∫£ ƒë·ªãnh ph√¢n ph·ªëi chu·∫©n: Ph√¢n ph·ªëi ph·∫ßn d∆∞ kh√¥ng ho√†n to√†n chu·∫©n, ƒë·∫∑c bi·ªát ·ªü c√°c gi√° tr·ªã c·ª±c ƒë·∫°i v√† c·ª±c ti·ªÉu (ƒëu√¥i d·ªØ li·ªáu).

# X√°c ƒë·ªãnh gi√° tr·ªã ngo·∫°i lai b·∫±ng Cook's Distance
cooks_dist <- cooks.distance(md_bmi_update)
outliers <- which(cooks_dist > (4 / nrow(data_no_diabetes)))

# Lo·∫°i b·ªè c√°c d√≤ng ngo·∫°i lai
data_no_outliers <- data_no_diabetes[-outliers, ]

# Ch·∫°y l·∫°i m√¥ h√¨nh
md_bmi_no_outliers <- lm(bmi ~ high_bp*high_chol + high_bp*phys_activity +
                         high_bp*hvy_alcohol_consump + high_bp*gen_hlth + 
                         high_bp*diff_walk + high_chol*smoker + smoker*fruits + 
                         smoker*veggies + smoker*gen_hlth + smoker*diff_walk + 
                         chol_check*age + stroke*gen_hlth + stroke*phys_hlth + 
                         heart_diseaseor_attack + education + income + sex,
                         data = data_no_outliers)

# Ki·ªÉm tra l·∫°i ph·∫ßn d∆∞
qqnorm(residuals(md_bmi_no_outliers))
qqline(residuals(md_bmi_no_outliers), col = "red")

Nh·∫≠n x√©t:

  • C√°c ƒëi·ªÉm tr√™n bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì h·∫ßu h·∫øt n·∫±m g·∫ßn ƒë∆∞·ªùng ch√©o ƒë·ªè (ƒë∆∞·ªùng k·ª≥ v·ªçng), cho th·∫•y r·∫±ng d·ªØ li·ªáu m·∫´u c√≥ xu h∆∞·ªõng ph√π h·ª£p v·ªõi ph√¢n ph·ªëi chu·∫©n.

  • Ph√¢n ph·ªëi d·ªØ li·ªáu kh√° ph√π h·ª£p v·ªõi ph√¢n ph·ªëi chu·∫©n ·ªü ph·∫ßn gi·ªØa, nh∆∞ng c√≥ ƒë·ªô l·ªách nh·∫π ·ªü hai ƒë·∫ßu

C. Nh·∫≠n x√©t v√† ƒë∆∞a ra khuy·∫øn ngh·ªã v·ªõi BMI

1. V·ªÅ m√¥ h√¨nh

Nh·∫≠n x√©t:

  • M√¥ h√¨nh cu·ªëi c√πng ƒë·ªÉ ki·ªÉm tra s·ª± tuy·∫øn t√≠nh c·ªßa c√°c bi·∫øn kh√°c l√™n BMI l√†

    final_md <- lm(bmi ~ high_bp * high_chol + high_bp * phys_activity + high_bp * hvy_alcohol_consump + high_bp * gen_hlth + high_bp * diff_walk + high_chol * smoker + smoker * fruits + smoker * veggies + smoker * gen_hlth + smoker diff_walk + chol_check * age + stroke * gen_hlth + stroke * phys_hlth + heart_diseaseor_attack + education + income + sex, data = data_no_outliers)

  • High_bp (Huy·∫øt √°p cao) t√°c ƒë·ªông ƒë·∫øn BMI th√¥ng qua c√°c t∆∞∆°ng t√°c:

    • high_bp * high_chol: Huy·∫øt √°p cao v√† cholesterol cao c√≥ th·ªÉ c√πng tƒÉng nguy c∆° ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI.
    • high_bp * phys_activity: Ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông th·ªÉ ch·∫•t gi·∫£m ho·∫∑c kh√¥ng ƒë·ªß ·ªü ng∆∞·ªùi huy·∫øt √°p cao c√≥ th·ªÉ l√†m tƒÉng BMI.
    • high_bp * hvy_alcohol_consump: Ti√™u th·ª• r∆∞·ª£u n·∫∑ng v√† huy·∫øt √°p cao g√≥p ph·∫ßn l√†m tƒÉng BMI.
    • high_bp * gen_hlth: S·ª± k·∫øt h·ª£p gi·ªØa huy·∫øt √°p cao v√† s·ª©c kh·ªèe t·ªïng qu√°t k√©m l√†m tƒÉng BMI.
    • high_bp * diff_walk: Kh√≥ khƒÉn trong ƒëi l·∫°i k·∫øt h·ª£p v·ªõi huy·∫øt √°p cao c≈©ng l√† y·∫øu t·ªë ƒë√°ng k·ªÉ.

  • High_chol (Cholesterol cao) k·∫øt h·ª£p v·ªõi h√†nh vi h√∫t thu·ªëc (high_chol * smoker) ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI.

  • Smoker (H√∫t thu·ªëc l√°) h√∫t thu·ªëc t√°c ƒë·ªông ƒë·∫øn BMI qua nhi·ªÅu y·∫øu t·ªë kh√°c: smoker * fruits: Vi·ªác h√∫t thu·ªëc v√† thi·∫øu tr√°i c√¢y trong ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô ƒÉn g√≥p ph·∫ßn l√†m thay ƒë·ªïi BMI.

    • smoker * veggies: T∆∞∆°ng t·ª±, s·ª± thi·∫øu rau c·ªß c√πng v·ªõi h√∫t thu·ªëc l√†m tƒÉng BMI.
    • smoker * gen_hlth: S·ª©c kh·ªèe t·ªïng qu√°t k√©m c·ªßa ng∆∞·ªùi h√∫t thu·ªëc ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng l·ªõn ƒë·∫øn BMI.
    • smoker * diff_walk: Kh√≥ khƒÉn ƒëi l·∫°i c≈©ng c√≥ t√°c ƒë·ªông ti√™u c·ª±c khi k·∫øt h·ª£p v·ªõi h√∫t thu·ªëc.

  • Chol_check (Ki·ªÉm tra cholesterol) k·∫øt h·ª£p v·ªõi tu·ªïi (chol_check * age), cho th·∫•y tu·ªïi t√°c c√πng t·∫ßm so√°t cholesterol c√≥ ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI.

  • Stroke v√† Heart_diseaseor_attack (ƒê·ªôt qu·ªµ v√† b·ªánh tim) nh·ªØng ng∆∞·ªùi t·ª´ng b·ªã ƒë·ªôt qu·ªµ ho·∫∑c b·ªánh tim c√≥ th·ªÉ c√≥ BMI kh√°c bi·ªát do ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn s·ª©c kh·ªèe t·ªïng qu√°t v√† ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông th·ªÉ ch·∫•t.

  • Education (Tr√¨nh ƒë·ªô h·ªçc v·∫•n) tr√¨nh ƒë·ªô h·ªçc v·∫•n c√≥ th·ªÉ ph·∫£n √°nh th√≥i quen s·ªëng l√†nh m·∫°nh h∆°n (ƒÉn u·ªëng, ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông th·ªÉ ch·∫•t) v√† t·ª´ ƒë√≥ ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI.

  • Income (Thu nh·∫≠p) thu nh·∫≠p cao c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒëi k√®m v·ªõi kh·∫£ nƒÉng ti·∫øp c·∫≠n th·ª±c ph·∫©m ch·∫•t l∆∞·ª£ng ho·∫∑c ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô s·ªëng l√†nh m·∫°nh h∆°n, ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI.

  • Sex (Gi·ªõi t√≠nh) ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn BMI qua s·ª± kh√°c bi·ªát v·ªÅ sinh h·ªçc, h√†nh vi, v√† c√°c y·∫øu t·ªë vƒÉn h√≥a.

K·∫øt lu·∫≠n

  • BMI ch·ªãu ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng c·ªßa nhi·ªÅu y·∫øu t·ªë li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn s·ª©c kh·ªèe (nh∆∞ huy·∫øt √°p, cholesterol, ƒë·ªôt qu·ªµ), h√†nh vi c√° nh√¢n (nh∆∞ h√∫t thu·ªëc, ti√™u th·ª• r∆∞·ª£u, ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô ƒÉn), v√† c√°c ƒë·∫∑c ƒëi·ªÉm nh√¢n kh·∫©u h·ªçc (gi·ªõi t√≠nh, thu nh·∫≠p, tr√¨nh ƒë·ªô h·ªçc v·∫•n).

  • T∆∞∆°ng t√°c gi·ªØa c√°c bi·∫øn: M√¥ h√¨nh ch·ªâ ra r·∫±ng nhi·ªÅu y·∫øu t·ªë kh√¥ng ch·ªâ ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng tr·ª±c ti·∫øp ƒë·∫øn BMI m√† c√≤n c√≥ s·ª± t∆∞∆°ng t√°c ph·ª©c t·∫°p, v√≠ d·ª• nh∆∞ s·ª± k·∫øt h·ª£p gi·ªØa huy·∫øt √°p cao, cholesterol, v√† c√°c h√†nh vi l·ªëi s·ªëng.

  • T√°c ƒë·ªông c·ªßa s·ª©c kh·ªèe t·ªïng qu√°t: C√°c bi·∫øn nh∆∞ s·ª©c kh·ªèe t·ªïng qu√°t (gen_hlth), kh√≥ khƒÉn ƒëi l·∫°i (diff_walk) ph·∫£n √°nh r√µ r·ªát t√°c ƒë·ªông c·ªßa t√¨nh tr·∫°ng s·ª©c kh·ªèe chung l√™n BMI.

2. Khuy·∫øn ngh·ªã ƒë·ªÉ c·∫£i thi·ªán BMI

  • Ki·ªÉm so√°t huy·∫øt √°p v√† cholesterol
  • Gi·∫£m ho·∫∑c ng·ª´ng h√∫t thu·ªëc
  • H·∫°n ch·∫ø ti√™u th·ª• r∆∞·ª£u bia
  • TƒÉng c∆∞·ªùng ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông th·ªÉ ch·∫•t
  • C·∫£i thi·ªán ch·∫ø ƒë·ªô ƒÉn u·ªëng
  • S·ªëng l√†nh m·∫°nh

Classification

S·ª≠ d·ª•ng c√°c ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p ph√¢n lo·∫°i ƒë·ªÉ d·ª± ƒëo√°n t√¨nh tr·∫°ng b·ªánh ti·ªÉu ƒë∆∞·ªùng c·ªßa b·ªánh nh√¢n. ### 1.X·ª≠ l√Ω d·ªØ li·ªáu #### 1.1 L∆∞·ª£c b·ªè c√°c bi·∫øn D·ª±a v√†o k·∫øt qu·∫£ c·ªßa ki·ªÉm ƒë·ªãnh Chi b√¨nh ph∆∞∆°ng ·ªü tr√™n, ta th·∫•y c√°c bi·∫øn ‚Äúgen_hlth‚Äù,‚Äúincome‚Äù,‚Äúeducation‚Äù, ‚Äúage‚Äù ƒë·ªôc l·∫≠p v·ªõi bi·∫øn diabetes_012.

S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng ng∆∞·ªùi ·ªü nh√≥m 0 cao h∆°n r·∫•t nhi·ªÅu so v·ªõi s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng ng∆∞·ªùi ·ªü nh√≥m 1 v√† nh√≥m 2 n√™n ch√∫ng ta c·∫ßn ph·∫£i x·ª≠ l√Ω d·ªØ li·ªáu b·ªã m·∫•t c√¢n b·∫±ng n√†y. #### 1.3.1 Ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p under-sampling

under_sampling_3c <- function(data, name_class) {
  # ƒê·∫£m b·∫£o c·ªôt ph√¢n lo·∫°i l√† vector v√† sau ƒë√≥ chuy·ªÉn th√†nh factor
  class_fact <- as.factor(data[[name_class]])
  
  # T√°ch d·ªØ li·ªáu th√†nh c√°c nh√≥m d·ª±a tr√™n nh√£n l·ªõp
  data_split <- split(data, class_fact)
  
  # S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u trong t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  n_class <- sapply(data_split, nrow)
  n_minor <- min(n_class)  # S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u nh·ªè nh·∫•t
  
  # Gi·∫£m m·∫´u cho t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  sampled_data <- lapply(data_split, function(class_data) {
    if (nrow(class_data) > n_minor) {
      # Ch·ªçn ng·∫´u nhi√™n n_minor m·∫´u n·∫øu s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng v∆∞·ª£t qu√° n_minor
      sampled_rows <- sample(seq_len(nrow(class_data)), size = n_minor, replace = FALSE)
      class_data <- class_data[sampled_rows, ]
    }
    return(class_data)
  })
  
  # K·∫øt h·ª£p l·∫°i c√°c l·ªõp
  new_data <- do.call(rbind, sampled_data)
  rownames(new_data) <- NULL  # Reset ch·ªâ s·ªë d√≤ng
  return(new_data)
}

data_under <- under_sampling_3c(data, "diabetes_012")
table(data_under$diabetes_012)
## 
##    0    1    2 
## 4631 4631 4631

1.3.2 Ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p over-sampling

over_sampling_multi <- function(data, name_class) {
# Chuy·ªÉn c·ªôt class th√†nh factor
class_fact <- as.factor(data[[name_class]])

# Chia d·ªØ li·ªáu theo t·ª´ng nh√≥m
data_split <- split(data, class_fact)

# ƒê·∫øm s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u c·ªßa t·ª´ng nh√≥m
n_class <- sapply(data_split, FUN = nrow)

# X√°c ƒë·ªãnh s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u l·ªõn nh·∫•t
n_max <- max(n_class)

# TƒÉng c∆∞·ªùng m·∫´u cho t·ª´ng nh√≥m
new_data <- do.call(rbind, lapply(names(data_split), function(class_name) {
group_data <- data_split[[class_name]]
n_samples <- nrow(group_data)

# N·∫øu nh√≥m c√≥ √≠t h∆°n n_max, th·ª±c hi·ªán over-sampling
if (n_samples < n_max) {
id_samples <- sample(1:n_samples, size = n_max, replace = TRUE)
group_data <- group_data[id_samples, ]
}

return(group_data)
}))

return(new_data)
}
# √Åp d·ª•ng ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p over-sampling
data_over <- over_sampling_multi(data, "diabetes_012")
# Ki·ªÉm tra s·ª± m·∫•t c√¢n b·∫±ng d·ªØ li·ªáu (imbalanced data) cho bi·∫øn m·ª•c ti√™u "diabetes_012"
imbalanced_summary <- table(data_over$diabetes_012)
print(imbalanced_summary)
## 
##      0      1      2 
## 213703 213703 213703
ggplot(data_over, aes(x = diabetes_012 , fill = as.factor(diabetes_012))) +
  geom_bar(position = "stack") +  # Hi·ªÉn th·ªã s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng
  labs(
    title = "Stacked Bar Chart for diabetes_012",
    x = "Groups",
    y = "Count",
    fill = "Diabetes Status"
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#66c2a5", "#fc8d62", "#8da0cb")) +
  theme_minimal()

1.4 Chia v√† chu·∫©n h√≥a d·ªØ li·ªáu

# H√†m chia d·ªØ li·ªáu th√†nh train v√† test
split_random <- function(data, target_col, train_ratio = 0.7) {
  set.seed(86)  # ƒê·∫∑t seed ƒë·ªÉ ƒë·∫£m b·∫£o t√≠nh t√°i l·∫≠p
  train_index <- createDataPartition(data[[target_col]], p = train_ratio, list = FALSE)
  train_data <- data[train_index, ]
  test_data <- data[-train_index, ]
  list(train = train_data, test = test_data)
}

# H√†m chu·∫©n h√≥a d·ªØ li·ªáu (Min-Max Scaling)
normalize_data <- function(train_data, test_data, cols) {
  for (col in cols) {
    min_val <- min(train_data[[col]], na.rm = TRUE)
    max_val <- max(train_data[[col]], na.rm = TRUE)
    
    # Chu·∫©n h√≥a t·∫≠p hu·∫•n luy·ªán
    train_data[[col]] <- (train_data[[col]] - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)
    
    # Chu·∫©n h√≥a t·∫≠p ki·ªÉm tra
    test_data[[col]] <- (test_data[[col]] - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)
  }
  list(train = train_data, test = test_data)
}

# C√°c c·ªôt ƒë·ªãnh l∆∞·ª£ng c·∫ßn chu·∫©n h√≥a
continuous_cols <- c("bmi", "ment_hlth", "phys_hlth")

# √Åp d·ª•ng cho t·ª´ng t·∫≠p d·ªØ li·ªáu (data_under, data_over, data_smote)
datasets <- list(under = data_under, over = data_over, smote = data_smote)

# K·∫øt qu·∫£ sau khi chia v√† chu·∫©n h√≥a
processed_data <- lapply(datasets, function(dataset) {
  # Chia d·ªØ li·ªáu th√†nh train v√† test
  split <- split_random(dataset, target_col = "diabetes_012", train_ratio = 0.7)
  # Chu·∫©n h√≥a d·ªØ li·ªáu
  normalize_data(split$train, split$test, continuous_cols)
})


# Truy c·∫≠p k·∫øt qu·∫£ cho t·ª´ng t·∫≠p d·ªØ li·ªáu
train_data_under <- processed_data$under$train
test_data_under <- processed_data$under$test

train_data_over <- processed_data$over$train
test_data_over <- processed_data$over$test

train_data_smote <- processed_data$smote$train
test_data_smote <- processed_data$smote$test

V·∫Ω ROC v√† t√≠nh AUC ƒë·ªÉ ƒë√°nh gi√° 3 m√¥ h√¨nh tr√™n.

# H√†m t√≠nh v√† v·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC
plot_roc <- function(model, test_data, target_col) {
  # Lo·∫°i c·ªôt m·ª•c ti√™u kh·ªèi d·ªØ li·ªáu ki·ªÉm tra
  newdata <- test_data[, !(colnames(test_data) == target_col)]
  
  # T√≠nh to√°n x√°c su·∫•t d·ª± ƒëo√°n
  prob_predictions <- predict(model, newdata, type = "raw")
  
  # Chuy·ªÉn c·ªôt m·ª•c ti√™u th√†nh d·∫°ng numeric
  actual_classes <- as.numeric(test_data[[target_col]]) - 1
  
  # V·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC cho t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  roc_list <- lapply(1:ncol(prob_predictions), function(class_index) {
    roc(response = actual_classes == (class_index - 1), 
        predictor = prob_predictions[, class_index], 
        levels = c(FALSE, TRUE), 
        direction = "<")
  })
  
  # V·∫Ω c√°c ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC tr√™n c√πng m·ªôt bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì
  plot(roc_list[[1]], col = "red", main = "ROC Curve for Classes", legacy.axes = TRUE)
  for (i in 2:length(roc_list)) {
    plot(roc_list[[i]], col = i + 1, add = TRUE)
  }
  
  # Th√™m ch√∫ th√≠ch
  legend("bottomright", legend = paste("Class", 0:(length(roc_list) - 1)), 
         col = 2:(length(roc_list) + 1), lwd = 2)
  
  # T√≠nh v√† in AUC cho t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  auc_values <- sapply(roc_list, function(roc) auc(roc))
  print(paste("AUC for each class:", auc_values))
}

# V·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC cho d·ªØ li·ªáu under-sampling
cat("Under-sampling:\n")
## Under-sampling:
plot_roc(nb_model, test_data_under, "diabetes_012")

## [1] "AUC for each class: 0.770503197757138"
## [2] "AUC for each class: 0.632131848458603"
## [3] "AUC for each class: 0.714270849692716"
# V·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC cho d·ªØ li·ªáu over-sampling
cat("\nOver-sampling:\n")
## 
## Over-sampling:
plot_roc(nb_model, test_data_over, "diabetes_012")

## [1] "AUC for each class: 0.777531377885668"
## [2] "AUC for each class: 0.635618984608642"
## [3] "AUC for each class: 0.715772434028911"
# V·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC cho d·ªØ li·ªáu SMOTE
cat("\nSMOTE:\n")
## 
## SMOTE:
plot_roc(nb_model, test_data_smote, "diabetes_012")

## [1] "AUC for each class: 0.769111452940434"
## [2] "AUC for each class: 0.63332027669161" 
## [3] "AUC for each class: 0.718919619647939"

2.2 Ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p Discriminant Analysis

2.2.1 Linear Discriminant Analysis

# H√†m ƒë√°nh gi√°
eval_multi_class <- function(conf_matrix) {
  cc <- sum(diag(conf_matrix))
  sc <- sum(conf_matrix)
  pp <- colSums(conf_matrix)
  tt <- rowSums(conf_matrix)
  
  prec <- diag(conf_matrix) / colSums(conf_matrix)
  recall <- diag(conf_matrix) / rowSums(conf_matrix)
  macro_prec <- mean(prec, na.rm = TRUE)
  macro_recall <- mean(recall, na.rm = TRUE)
  macro_f1 <- 2 * macro_prec * macro_recall / (macro_prec + macro_recall)
  acc <- cc / sc
  kap <- (cc * sc - sum(pp * tt)) / (sc^2 - sum(pp * tt))
  
  list(
    Precision = prec,
    Recall = recall,
    Accuracy = acc,
    Kappa = kap,
    Macro_F1 = macro_f1
  )
}
# H√†m t√≠nh v√† v·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC
plot_roc <- function(prob_predictions, actual_classes) {
  # V·∫Ω ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC cho t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  roc_list <- lapply(1:ncol(prob_predictions), function(class_index) {
    roc(response = actual_classes == (class_index - 1), 
        predictor = prob_predictions[, class_index], 
        levels = c(FALSE, TRUE), 
        direction = "<")
  })
  
  # V·∫Ω c√°c ƒë∆∞·ªùng ROC tr√™n c√πng m·ªôt bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì
  plot(roc_list[[1]], col = "red", main = "ROC Curve for Classes", legacy.axes = TRUE)
  for (i in 2:length(roc_list)) {
    plot(roc_list[[i]], col = i + 1, add = TRUE)
  }
  
  # Th√™m ch√∫ th√≠ch
  legend("bottomright", legend = paste("Class", 0:(length(roc_list) - 1)), 
         col = 2:(length(roc_list) + 1), lwd = 2)
  
  # T√≠nh v√† in AUC cho t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  auc_values <- sapply(roc_list, function(roc) auc(roc))
  print(paste("AUC for each class:", auc_values))
}

Th·ª±c hi·ªán v·ªõi b·ªô d·ªØ li·ªáu ƒë∆∞·ª£c x·ª≠ l√Ω b·∫±ng ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p under-sampling:

## [1] 0.1346902
eval_multi_class <- function(x) {
  if (!is.matrix(x) && !inherits(x, "table")) {
    stop("l·ªói")
  }
  

  if (inherits(x, "table")) {
    x <- as.matrix(x)
  }

  # T√≠nh to√°n c√°c th√¥ng s·ªë
  cc <- sum(diag(x))  # T·ªïng s·ªë d·ª± ƒëo√°n ƒë√∫ng
  sc <- sum(x)        # T·ªïng s·ªë ph·∫ßn t·ª≠
  pp <- colSums(x)    # T·ªïng s·ªë ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ trong t·ª´ng c·ªôt
  tt <- rowSums(x)    # T·ªïng s·ªë ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ trong t·ª´ng h√†ng

  # Precision v√† Recall
  prec <- diag(x) / colSums(x)
  recall <- diag(x) / rowSums(x)
  macro_prec <- mean(prec, na.rm = TRUE)
  macro_recall <- mean(recall, na.rm = TRUE)

  # F1-score
  macro_f1 <- 2 * macro_prec * macro_recall / (macro_prec + macro_recall)

  # Accuracy
  acc <- cc / sc

  # Kappa statistic
  kap <- (cc * sc - sum(pp * tt)) / (sc^2 - sum(pp * tt))

  # Tr·∫£ v·ªÅ k·∫øt qu·∫£
  return(list(
    Precision = prec,
    Recall = recall,
    Accuracy = acc,
    Kappa = kap,
    Macro_F1 = macro_f1
  ))
}


# T√≠nh to√°n c√°c ch·ªâ s·ªë cho t·∫≠p hu·∫•n luy·ªán

print(result_under_train)

acc_class_under_test
## [1] 0.524598
eval_multi_class <- function(x) {
  if (!is.matrix(x) && !inherits(x, "table")) {
    stop("Input ph·∫£i l√† ma tr·∫≠n ho·∫∑c b·∫£ng t·∫ßn su·∫•t!")
  }
  
  if (inherits(x, "table")) {
    x <- as.matrix(x)
  }

  # Chu·∫©n h√≥a ma tr·∫≠n n·∫øu c·∫ßn
  sc <- sum(x)  # T·ªïng s·ªë ph·∫ßn t·ª≠
  if (sc > 1e7) {  # N·∫øu t·ªïng qu√° l·ªõn, chu·∫©n h√≥a ma tr·∫≠n
    x <- x / sc
    message("Ma tr·∫≠n ƒë∆∞·ª£c chu·∫©n h√≥a ƒë·ªÉ tr√°nh overflow.")
  }
  
  # T√≠nh to√°n c√°c th√¥ng s·ªë
  cc <- sum(diag(x))  # T·ªïng s·ªë d·ª± ƒëo√°n ƒë√∫ng
  pp <- colSums(x)    # T·ªïng s·ªë ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ trong t·ª´ng c·ªôt
  tt <- rowSums(x)    # T·ªïng s·ªë ph·∫ßn t·ª≠ trong t·ª´ng h√†ng

  # Precision v√† Recall
  prec <- diag(x) / colSums(x)
  recall <- diag(x) / rowSums(x)
  macro_prec <- mean(prec, na.rm = TRUE)
  macro_recall <- mean(recall, na.rm = TRUE)

  # F1-score
  macro_f1 <- 2 * macro_prec * macro_recall / (macro_prec + macro_recall)

  # Accuracy
  acc <- cc / sc

  # T√≠nh Kappa
  expected_accuracy <- sum(tt * pp) / sc^2
  kappa <- (acc - expected_accuracy) / (1 - expected_accuracy)

  # Tr·∫£ v·ªÅ k·∫øt qu·∫£
  return(list(
    Precision = prec,
    Recall = recall,
    Accuracy = acc,
    Macro_F1 = macro_f1,
    Kappa = kappa
  ))
}

## #   ment_hlth <dbl>, phys_hlth <dbl>, diff_walk <fct>, sex <fct>
under_sampling_3c <- function(data, name_class) {
  # ƒê·∫£m b·∫£o c·ªôt ph√¢n lo·∫°i l√† vector v√† sau ƒë√≥ chuy·ªÉn th√†nh factor
  class_fact <- as.factor(data[[name_class]])
  
  # T√°ch d·ªØ li·ªáu th√†nh c√°c nh√≥m d·ª±a tr√™n nh√£n l·ªõp
  data_split <- split(data, class_fact)
  
  # S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u trong t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  n_class <- sapply(data_split, nrow)
  n_minor <- min(n_class)  # S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u nh·ªè nh·∫•t
  
  # Gi·∫£m m·∫´u cho t·ª´ng l·ªõp
  sampled_data <- lapply(data_split, function(class_data) {
    if (nrow(class_data) > n_minor) {
      # Ch·ªçn ng·∫´u nhi√™n n_minor m·∫´u n·∫øu s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng v∆∞·ª£t qu√° n_minor
      sampled_rows <- sample(seq_len(nrow(class_data)), size = n_minor, replace = FALSE)
      class_data <- class_data[sampled_rows, ]
    }
    return(class_data)
  })
  
  # K·∫øt h·ª£p l·∫°i c√°c l·ªõp
  new_data <- do.call(rbind, sampled_data)
  rownames(new_data) <- NULL  # Reset ch·ªâ s·ªë d√≤ng
  return(new_data)
}

data_under <- under_sampling_3c(data, "diabetes_012")

over_sampling_multi <- function(data, name_class) {
# Chuy·ªÉn c·ªôt class th√†nh factor
class_fact <- as.factor(data[[name_class]])

# Chia d·ªØ li·ªáu theo t·ª´ng nh√≥m
data_split <- split(data, class_fact)

# ƒê·∫øm s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u c·ªßa t·ª´ng nh√≥m
n_class <- sapply(data_split, FUN = nrow)

# X√°c ƒë·ªãnh s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng m·∫´u l·ªõn nh·∫•t
n_max <- max(n_class)

# TƒÉng c∆∞·ªùng m·∫´u cho t·ª´ng nh√≥m
new_data <- do.call(rbind, lapply(names(data_split), function(class_name) {
group_data <- data_split[[class_name]]
n_samples <- nrow(group_data)

# N·∫øu nh√≥m c√≥ √≠t h∆°n n_max, th·ª±c hi·ªán over-sampling
if (n_samples < n_max) {
id_samples <- sample(1:n_samples, size = n_max, replace = TRUE)
group_data <- group_data[id_samples, ]
}

return(group_data)
}))

return(new_data)
}
# √Åp d·ª•ng ph∆∞∆°ng ph√°p over-sampling
data_over <- over_sampling_multi(data, "diabetes_012")
data_smote = smotenc(df = data, var = "diabetes_012",
k = 5, over_ratio = 1)
# H√†m chia d·ªØ li·ªáu th√†nh train v√† test
split_random <- function(data, target_col, train_ratio = 0.7) {
  set.seed(86)  # ƒê·∫∑t seed ƒë·ªÉ ƒë·∫£m b·∫£o t√≠nh t√°i l·∫≠p
  train_index <- createDataPartition(data[[target_col]], p = train_ratio, list = FALSE)
  train_data <- data[train_index, ]
  test_data <- data[-train_index, ]
  list(train = train_data, test = test_data)
}

# H√†m chu·∫©n h√≥a d·ªØ li·ªáu (Min-Max Scaling)
normalize_data <- function(train_data, test_data, cols) {
  for (col in cols) {
    min_val <- min(train_data[[col]], na.rm = TRUE)
    max_val <- max(train_data[[col]], na.rm = TRUE)
    
    # Chu·∫©n h√≥a t·∫≠p hu·∫•n luy·ªán
    train_data[[col]] <- (train_data[[col]] - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)
    
    # Chu·∫©n h√≥a t·∫≠p ki·ªÉm tra
    test_data[[col]] <- (test_data[[col]] - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)
  }
  list(train = train_data, test = test_data)
}

# C√°c c·ªôt ƒë·ªãnh l∆∞·ª£ng c·∫ßn chu·∫©n h√≥a
continuous_cols <- c("bmi", "ment_hlth", "phys_hlth")

# √Åp d·ª•ng cho t·ª´ng t·∫≠p d·ªØ li·ªáu (data_under, data_over, data_smote)
datasets <- list(under = data_under, over = data_over, smote = data_smote)

# K·∫øt qu·∫£ sau khi chia v√† chu·∫©n h√≥a
processed_data <- lapply(datasets, function(dataset) {
  # Chia d·ªØ li·ªáu th√†nh train v√† test
  split <- split_random(dataset, target_col = "diabetes_012", train_ratio = 0.7)
  # Chu·∫©n h√≥a d·ªØ li·ªáu
  normalize_data(split$train, split$test, continuous_cols)
})
